2. In this Act-                                                           Interpreta-
                                                                            tion.
“land” means          all hereditaments corporeal               and   in-
    corporeal;
“personal representative” means an executor or adminis-
    trator who has obtained probate or letters of adminis-
    tration;
“the Court” means the Supreme Court, or any Judge thereof;
     and in cases within the jurisdiction of any Resident
     Magistrate’s Court, the Judge of such Court;
“prescribed” means prescribed by rules of court;
“registered land” means land registered under the
     Registration of Titles Act.
